CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "Tres Chic are these three lovelies who will aid and model for the exclusive D.I. Club when it gives its annual benefit to aid the National Foundation (formerly Infantile Paralysis). Janice Dent, Nadine Primas and Mary Ann Ritter were three who enjoyed a champagne party given at the home of D.I. Gloria Grate.  The March of Dimes extravaganza is due for a Jan. 3 showing at the plush New Arena at 5 p.m. with Wild Bill Davis on hand for the magnificent show and dancing.  Tickets, $4 per person, may be secured from any member of the club, Gay DeHall, president; Rubye Young  Buchanan, Juanita Drake, Nellye Barron, Gloria Grate and new pledge member Doryce Griffin. - Harris Photo. - Adv."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of D. I. Club members Janice Dent, Nadine Primas and Mary Ann Ritter, standing in home of Gloria Golden Grate, possibly at 7413 Strananhan, for champagne party
